(79, 'Philodendron Ginny with Totem', 'The deep green leaves on the Philodendron \'Ginny\' (Rhaphidophora tetrasperma) look like a smaller version of the Monstera deliciosa. They grow 6-inch split lobes depending on the supply of bright, indirect light. This plant is in the family of Araceae (neither Monstera nor Philodendron) and prefers climbing rather than hanging. Supply them with a moss pole or plant tape for support as it ...', 'philodendron-ginny-with-totem', 71, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/Pl_6in_Totem-Philodendron-Ginny_Detail_02_large.jpg?v=1689009843', 1140000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(80, 'Philodendron Prince of Orange', 'All rise! A new member of the royal family has arrived... The Philodendron \'Prince of Orange\' is a vibrant and eye-catching heir to the crown, known for its stunning foliage that changes color as it matures. The unique leaves start off a bright copper-orange color and gradually turn to a deep green. Long may he reign!', 'philodendron-prince-of-orange', 80, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/Pl_4in_Philodendron-Prince-of-Orange_Detail_02_large.jpg?v=1718171545', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(81, 'Glazed Succulent Garden', 'These gardens of petite succulents are perfect for sprucing up your tablescapes or sunny windowsill. It\'s always a party with three assorted easy-care succulents planted together in a beautiful glazed ceramic pot. Perfectly giftable, perfectly keepable. Garden container is 5\" wide by 3\" tall.  *Succulent varieties and glaze color is assorted and may differ slightly from photos', 'glazed-succulent-garden', 52, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/Pl_Low-Bowl-Garden-Glaze_Blue-Pot_02_2_large.jpg?v=1727410204', 870000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(82, 'Peperomia Ginny', 'The Peperomia species are members of the black pepper family. They are beautiful variegated foliage that has hints of red around the leaf edges to make them a stunner beside a conversation area. Keep them in warmer conditions with lots of humidity. Let the soil dry out between watering to keep this one thriving.', 'peperomia-ginny', 84, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/PeperomiaGinny_DTL2_large.jpg?v=1641656295', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(83, 'Philodendron Birkin Plant', 'The Philodendron \'Birkin\' foliage becomes more variegated as they mature and has an upright growth habit. As they unfurl, their leaves show tinges of pink and red. Their ovate leaf shape shows off stripes of white and deep emerald green. Although slow growers, they can reach 3 feet tall and wide, given adequate light and moisture.', 'philodendron-birkin-plant', 24, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/pl_unknown_4IN_po_grower_detail-1_large.jpg?v=1626820706', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(84, 'Baby Rubber Plant (Peperomia Obtusifolia)', 'The Baby Rubber Plant (Peperomia obtusifolia) is one of our shiniest new plants and oh so cute! She\'s adorable hanging in a container from a shelf or basket. She loves being a part of a wall of greenery and does well as a low-maintenance must-have for all your beginner gardening friends. Her leaves are succulent-like, which hold moisture in for longer. She\'s a \'Plant of Merit\' crowned by the ...', 'baby-rubber-plant-(peperomia-obtusifolia)', 64, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/pl_pepperomiaobtusifolia_6IN_po_basket-detail-1_large.jpg?v=1634573541', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(85, 'Arcadia Phalaenopsis Orchid', 'Behold the beauty of the Arcadia Phalaenopsis Orchid, a masterpiece crafted by nature itself! This exotic moth orchid boasts not one but TWO stunning flower spikes ensuring it always steals the show. The best part is that these blooms can last up to 3 months!  We ship our orchids in partial bloom, which means you\'ll see some flowers that haven\'t entirely opened up yet. The actual color of ...', 'arcadia-phalaenopsis-orchid', 55, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/Pl_5in_Phalaenopsis-Arcadia-Orchid_Detail_01_large.jpg?v=1713237478', 960000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(86, 'Umbrella Tree Plant (Schefflera Gold Capella)', 'One of the fastest-growing houseplants, Umbrella Plants, can be kept short and bushy or grow all the way up. Add some height to your indoor jungle with our unique umbrella tree. They are one of our favorite beginner plants. Not only are they low maintenance, but they also grow quickly. They can grow to ceiling-skimming heights of six feet and over, but if you prefer shorter shrubs, you can ...', 'umbrella-tree-plant-(schefflera-gold-capella)', 70, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/pl_ScheffleraGoldCapella_6IN_po_grower_detail-1_large.jpg?v=1656480930', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(87, 'Maidenhair Fern', 'With such bright and delicate fronds, the Maidenhair Fern is absolutely worth the extra effort! This diva prefers moist soil, low light and humid conditions but the extra TLC will pay off quick!', 'maidenhair-fern', 53, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/pl_MaidenhairFern_4IN_po_grower_detail-1_large.jpg?v=1658349301', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(88, 'Cat Palm', 'Enjoy the Chamaedorea Cataractarum (Cat Palm) as a low-growing palm with lots of fluff on their green stems. Create that \'by-gone day\' theme with the airy display of dark green leaves and leaflets. This palm even displays a bright yellow pendulous inflorescence in early spring with shiny fruit on the flower stalk. Enjoy them daily in bright, indirect light for years to come!', 'cat-palm', 96, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/ChinaDoll_10_4_DTL_d9fbaa94-1589-4a98-80d1-65aba87a2a1b_large.jpg?v=1611786311', 2040000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(89, 'European Cypress Christmas Tree', 'This handsome European cypress (Cupressus sempervirens) is a native in southern Europe and western Asia. His columnar form reaches to the sky in his native land to 40-60\' feet. His stately elegant and narrow appearance makes it a beloved garden punctuation point in classical Italian gardens during the Renaissance. When crushed, the dark grayish-green foliage has an aromatic fragrance, making ...', 'european-cypress-christmas-tree', 46, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/4in_European-Cypress-Christmas-Tree_Detail_large.jpg?v=1732519942', 483750, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(90, 'White Phalaenopsis Orchid', 'The Audrey Hepburn of orchids, this beauty is classy, timeless, and always in style! To really wow us, this elegant queen boasts not one, but TWO stunning flower spikes. The best part is, these blooms can last up to 3 months! We ship our orchids in partial bloom, which means you\'ll see some flowers that haven\'t entirely opened up yet. The actual color of blooms may vary slightly from what is ...', 'white-phalaenopsis-orchid', 73, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/files/Pl_5in_pwhite-phalaenopsis-orchid_Detail_04_large.jpg?v=1713237632', 739500, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(91, 'Janet Craig Dragon Plant (Dracaena)', 'Try this virtually indestructible plant that thrives on low light and little water. The Dracaena Janet Craig is perfect for people on the go with little time to waste! They even earn their keep by cleaning the air of nasty toxins! Their sword-like dark green 3 inches wide and eventually two feet-long leaves fill out the mature stalk, giving you that tropical vibe in your casa.', 'janet-craig-dragon-plant-(dracaena)', 1, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/pl_JanetCraig_4IN_po_grower_detail-2_large.jpg?v=1632171442', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10'),
(92, 'Evita Vriesea Bromeliad', 'The impressive Evita Vriesea Bromeliad (Vriesea splendens) shows off its sword-shaped flower spike emerging from fiery stems. They don\'t bloom until they are aged three to five years. Expect the bracts to last several weeks to give a great show. Once they fade, pups will form, and propagation naturally begins to recreate the festive look in the future.   You will receive a beautiful surprise ...', 'evita-vriesea-bromeliad', 20, 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0068/4215/5090/products/pl_EvitaVrieseaBromeliad_4IN_po_grower_detail-1_large.jpg?v=1659114023', 645000, '2024-12-12 18:13:10', '2024-12-12 18:13:10');
